  "text": "Decreased expression of Cyp1a2 and Cyp2e1 mRNAs in tunicamycininjected mice suggests that ER stress might also activate RIDD, leading to the degradation of these mRNAs (Fig. 5 C) . To further investigate the link between the ER stress response and APAP metabolism, we characterized the phenotype of IRE1оҒЎdeficient mice, which were generated by crossing Ern1 flox mice with Mx1 cre transgenic mice. IRE1оҒЎ deletion in the liver was achieved by poly(I:C) injection, as done previously to generate Xbp1оҒ„ mice . Cremediated deletion of exons 20 and 21 of Ern1 caused an inframe deletion of 64 aa (aa 844-907) in the ribonuclease domain of IRE1оҒЎ, which completely abolished its ribonuclease activity, thus abrogating XBP1 mRNA splicing in the mutant mice (Fig. 7, A and B ; [CITATION_1] . Consistent with what we observed in Xbp1оҒ„ mice , ablation of IRE1оҒЎ abolished the induction of XBP1dependent UPR genes such as ERdj4 and Sec61оҒЎ in the liver of tunicamycininjected mice (Fig. 7 C) . Expression of CHOP, which is known to be regulated pri marily by the PERK pathway, was not significantly altered in IRE1оҒЎdeficient liver at the basal state or after tunicamy cin treatment (Fig. 7 C) . Notably, however, hepatic Cyp1a2 and Cyp2e1 mRNA levels were comparable between WT and Ern1оҒ„ mice, in contrast to the significant reduction of these mRNAs in XBP1deficient mouse liver. Further, Cyp1a2 and Cyp2e1 mRNAs were markedly decreased by tunicamycin treatment in WT but not IRE1оҒЎdeficient mice, indicating that these mRNAs were downregulated by IRE1оҒЎ in response to ER stress (Fig. 7 C) . Consistent with the normal expression of Cyp1a2 and Cyp2e1 mRNAs in Ern1оҒ„ mice, APAPinduced hepatotoxicity was comparable between WT and IRE1оҒЎdeficient mice, as assessed by serum ALT levels and histological analysis (Fig. 7, D and E) . However, Ern1оҒ„ mice were not more sensitive to APAPinduced hepatotoxicity than WT mice when challenged with a reduced dose of APAP, prompted us to test if the constitutively active IRE1оҒЎ in duced the degradation of Cyp1a2 and Cyp2e1 mRNAs in XBP1deficient liver. Liver lysates of WT and Xbp1 LKO mice (KO) were prepared and pooled for Western blot analysis using anti-APAP, anti-phospho-JNK, and total JNK antibodies. (C) Liver lysates from individual mice treated with APAP for 24 h or left untreated (NT) were subjected to Western blot analysis. Note that the blot was exposed to x-ray film longer than in B to increase the sensitivity.",
